25|$|Sanctification is {{the part}} of {{salvation}} in which God makes <b>the</b> <b>believer</b> holy, by enabling them to exercise greater love for God and for other people. The good works accomplished by believers as they are sanctified are considered to be the necessary outworking of <b>the</b> <b>believer's</b> salvation, though they do not cause <b>the</b> <b>believer</b> to be saved. Sanctification, like justification, is by faith, because doing good works is simply living as the son of God one has become.|$|R
